Peru Stocks: Cerro Verde, Maple, Minsur, Panoro, Southern Copper

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-08-02T21:05:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/peru-stocks-cerro-verde-maple-minsur-panoro-southern-copper.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index fell 1.1 percent to 21,710.28. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 1.2 percent to 2,691.74.  Miners slumped as metals declined in New York and  London ,
said Maher Saba, the chief analyst at Lima-based brokerage
Compass SAB.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, fell 3.9 percent to 3.65 soles.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO) 
, Peru’s biggest copper producer, dropped 3.9 percent
to $33.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and
gold exploration company, slid 3.6 percent to 53 cents. Sociedad
Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan
Copper & Gold Inc., fell 2.1 percent to $43.39.  Fuel refiners dropped after crude futures in New York
declined for a third day.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, fell 4.1 percent to $1.16.
Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol
YPF SA known as Relapasa, dropped 2.2 percent to 91 centimos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
